<HEADLINE> Aoshen Out-shoot Northeast Tigers in China Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Ma Jian hit four 3-pointers
to lead Beijing to a 111-100 victory over Jilin Northeast Tigers
while three-time defending champion Bayi Rockets crushed Sichuan
Pandas 125-104 in the second round competition of the Hilton C
hina Basketball League on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ma Jian, a two-time candidate in NBA try-out campus in 1995
and 1996, held off a strong late rally from the Tigers by hitting
consecutive 3-pointers in the mid of the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Aoshen led the first half 65-44 and outshot their
rivals 9-6 from the lang range.
</P>
<P>
A quick and accurate Jinan Army Pegasus upset the one the
tournament favorites Shandong Flaming Bulls 89-86. After jumping
at a 47-38 half break lead, the faster Pegasus took the advantage
to steal their first victory in the last 50 seconds when Bulls l
eague MVP Gong Xiaobin was fouled out with a game high 28
points.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jinsong scored 32 points to led the defending champion
Bayi Rockets to their second consecutive win in as many outings.
The Rockets, seeking their fourth straight CBA title, soared to a
comfortable lead of 68-40.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Ducks comeback from a stunning 103-98 overtime
defeat by Zhejiang Cyclone in their season opener last Sunday and
beat Jiangsu Dragons 87-82. The Ducks twin-towers of 2.10m
Bateer and 2.14m Shan Tao out rebounded their Dragons rivals
53-44 and lead the first half by 47-43.
</P>
<P>
In other games played on Wednesday, Liaoning Hunters also
scored their second win from the first two round by beating
Zhejiang Cyclone 118-104. The Hunters, last year's finalists, led
the first half 65-47.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wenqi sunk a round high 34 points to lift Shanghai
Shakes to a 110-84 overwhelming win over Guangdong Tigers. The
Sharks, led 49-36 at halftime, also rolled to their second win
into the first two round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
