<HEADLINE> San Tome &AMP; Principe Appoints New Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- San Tome &AMP; Principe President
Miguel Trovoada has appointed former foreign minister Guilherme
Posser da Costa as the country's new prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Wednesday said Posser is vice chairman
of the Sao Tome &AMP; Principe Liberation Movement -- the Social
Democratic Party (MLSTP-PSD), which won majority seats in the
parliamentary elections held early November and therefore is
entitled to form the next cabinet.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the president dissolved the current cabinet
led by Braganca Neto but insisted that the cabinet remain on post
until the new prime minister is sworn in.
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old Posser is a professional diplomat. He became
foreign minister in 1987 and retained the post again in 1994.
</P>
