<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Construct 17 Soil Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The National Fertilizer
Industry Agency of Ethiopia announced here Wednesday that 17 soil
research laboratories will be constructed in the country over the
next 18 months.
</P>
<P>
Zekele Desalegn, general manager of the Agency, told local
press that four laboratories are already under construction at a
cost of about one million Birr (133,000 US Dollars) each.
</P>
<P>
Zekele said the laboratories will carry out study on soil
types in various areas of Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Bids will soon be announced for the construction of four other
research laboratories in the country, he said, adding that
feasibility studies are also underway to construct nine more
laboratories.
</P>
<P>
According to the general manager, the laboratories will each
have a capacity to test up to 2,000 soil samples per year.
</P>
<P>
Regional agriculture bureaux will manage the projects when
they go operational in June 2000, he said.
</P>
<P>
The fund for the construction of the 17 soil research
laboratories was obtained in loan from the World Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
