<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moldova: Foreign Trade Drops 14 Percent in 11 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The foreign trade dropped
14.3 percent to 1,532 billion U.S. dollars in the Republic of
Moldova, in the eleven months of the outgoing year, showed the
latest official statistics reached here.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Economics and Reforms, the
Moldovan exports decreased in average by 22.5 percent during this
period, while the imports by 8.4 percent. In September and
November the decline was "very felt": 51.8 and 50.6 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts attributed the decline to the financial crisis
in Russia, Moldova's number one trade partner with the 51 percent
share of all imports and 77 percent share of all exports.
</P>
<P>
Trade with the Commonwealth of Independent States in January
through November reduced by 26.1 percent, while with the West it
increased by 4.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The exports towards Romania, Italy, Austria, France, Canada and
the United States increased due to surpluses of sugar, meat, apple
juice, nuts, clothes.
</P>
<P>
Statistics data also showed Moldova with a trade deficit of
366.3 million dollars by December 1, which is 81.5 million up
compared with 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
