<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Destroys 121-kg Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania Wednesday
destroyed 121 kilograms of mandrax worth 240 million Shillings
(about 353,000 U.S. Dollars) under tight police guard.
</P>
<P>
The drugs, contained in 242 small bags, were destroyed in fire
after pouring kerosene in a hole dug up for this purpose in the
northern region of Tanga, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The drugs, believed to be destined for Zambia, were
intercepted by customs officials at the Horohoro post on the
Kenya-Tanzania border in 1993, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The drug destruction has been the biggest since 1994, when 319
bags of drugs worth 600 million Shillings were intercepted at the
same border point and later destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The incident was watched by Tanga Regional Police Commander
Alfred Tibaigana who represented the Inspector General of Police,
a national security custom officer, Tanga medical officer and
reporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
