<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 30 (Xinhua) -- In a 30-minute telephone
conversation with U.S. President Bill Clinton on Wednesday Russian
President Boris Yeltsin said that the use of force against Iraq is
unacceptable.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin confirmed the Russia's position that the U.S.-British
air strikes on Iraq were "unacceptable from the point of
international law, the UN Charter, the principles of partnership
and cooperation."
</P>
<P>
During the telephone conversation Yeltsin called for restoring
the unity of the U.N. Security Council and returning the Iraq
question to a political channel.
</P>
