According to the Russian presidential press service, Yeltsin
and Clinton agreed on the need to preserve and develop the
positive potential accumulated in Russian-U.S. relations over the
past few years.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders discussed preparations for the next regular
sessions of (the Russian Prime Minister) Primakov-(U.S. Vice
President)Gore commission and the visit of U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright to Moscow scheduled for the end of January,
1999.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin and Clinton, exchanging New Years greetings, also
pointed to the importance of the coming year for preserving the
atmosphere of confidence and further advancement of Russian-U.S
relations. 
