<HEADLINE> Russia Decides to Set Euro-Ruble Exchange Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of Russia
announced Wednesday that it will set the official exchange rate of
the euro to the ruble, the payments and settlements and financial
transactions in the euro as reserve currency starting from January
1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the euro to the ruble will be established
on the basis of the euro's rate to the U.S. dollar on
international currency markets, the Itar-Tass quoted the bank as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The official exchange rates of the national currencies to the
ruble will be established by the Bank of Russia on the basis of
the official rate of the euro to the ruble by using the rate at
which the euro is converted into each of the national currencies
of the member countries set as of December 31,1998.
</P>
<P>
The Moscow currency exchange on Tuesday announced that from
January 10, 1999 it will operate in non-cash transactions and stop
transaction operations in German mark, French franc, Italian lira
and Finnish mark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
