defense ministry, which he noted is its promise made during the
elections.
</P>
<P>
Under Sao Tome &AMP; Principe constitution, the president has the
right to lead the country's diplomatic, defense and security
policies, therefore, he has the right to interfere with the work
of the above-mentioned ministries. 
