<HEADLINE> Virtual University Launched on Net in Zhejiang Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 31 (Xinhua) -- More than 600 students from
three cities in Zhejiang Province will begin their campus life at
a university that exists only on the local computer network and
was launched today by Zhejiang University, the largest university
in China.
</P>
<P>
At this virtual university, lectures, seminars and all
multi-media academic material will be transmitted via the
Internet. Professors and students will be able to have electronic,
visual discussions through the computer screen, and students can
freely arrange their schedule to do research in the electronic
library or access previous lectures simply by clicking on whatever
they want.
</P>
<P>
Long-distance education is only dawning in China, and so far
the Chinese Ministry of Education has permitted only four
universities to install this method on a trial basis, including
prestigious Qinghua University in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
A total of 11 long-distance electronic education center are
expected to be established by next spring, covering all of
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang University's long-term goal is to have the provincial
electronic educational network available on every personal
computer in the region, making higher education easily accessible
to everyone.  
</P>
