<HEADLINE> Unity, Key to Successful Economic Recovery: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said Thursday that preserving the prevailing
stability, peace and the cooperation among Malaysians is the key
to ensuring the success of Malaysia's economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
1999, the final year of the second millennium and the 20th
century, is poised to test the resilience of Malaysians and as
such they should be prepared to take on the challenges, Mahathir
said in his New Year message aired over radio Television Malaysia
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
He said: "If we persevere, if we preserve the stability and
peace in the country and if we work together to carry out the
strategies for recovery which we have planned together, we'll
achieve success and give continued meaning to our independence."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said although 1998 was a problem-ridden year, it was
also a year of successes for the country. He cited the opening of
the Kuala Lumpur International Airport, reputedly the world's most
beautiful and most modern airport, the completion of the world's
tallest building -- the Petronas Twin Towers, hosting of the 16th
Commonwealth Games as successes.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir, however, reminded Malaysians to continue to be
vigilant against enemies out to recolonize the country, saying
certain powers would use whatever weapons and equipment they have
to divide Malaysians and take control of the country.
</P>
<P>
He also said outsiders would not cease trying to destroy the
Malaysian economy by scaring away not only the investors but also
the tourists through adverse reports.
</P>
<P>
He said it was crucial that the Malaysia Incorporated Concept,
which emphasized cooperation between the government, workers and
the private sector, be adhered to in handling eventualities.
</P>
<P>
He said economic recovery efforts would require support from
all Malaysians by way of their preserving the prevailing peace and
harmony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
