<HEADLINE> Shanghai Airport Marks 11-Year Safety Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Hongqiao
International Airport marked eleven consecutive years of flight
safety with the landing of a FM 2833 from Chongqing Municipality
tonight.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two overseas and domestic airlines are now operating out
of Hongqiao on more than 300 air routes, and an average of 300
planes take off and land there every day, of which 30 percent are
international flights.
</P>
<P>
Over 128,000 aircraft took off and landed at the airport this
year, and 13.7 million travelers and 560,000 tons of goods and
postal articles were transported in and out of Hongqiao. This
year, the airport increased its annual transport volume by 12.65
percent.  
