Committee for Supporting Iraq, which had also called for lifting
the sanctions imposed on Iraq following its 1990 invasion of
Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, the Jordanian government also urged the
U.S. to stop its military actions against Iraq, and to pursue a
diplomatic solution to the Iraqi crisis.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. embassy in Amman had been cordoned off since December
16, when the U.S-British forces began to launch four consecutive
rounds of air raids on Baghdad, which were triggered by what the
U.S said Iraq's failure to cooperate fully with U.N. inspectors.
