<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar bubbled
higher Thursday, gaining nearly a third of a U.S. cent to end
local trade for 1998 on a positive note.
</P>
<P>
Buying interest came from offshore as British pound sterling
was exchanged for Australian dollars ahead of the weekend
introduction of the euro, said Dale Felton, foreign exchange
manager with HSBC Markets.
</P>
<P>
The foreign exchange market was quite active during the early
half of the day, in contrast to thin trading in recent days, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished Thursday at 61.43 U.S. cents,
its intra-day high, and fell as low as 61.06 U.S. cents. It
closed at 61.12 U.S. cents Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A year ago Thursday the Australian currency finished trading at
65.24 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished trading at 70.55 Japanese yen
from Wednesday's close of 70.48 yen and 1.0298 German marks from
1.0224 marks. 
