<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close on Strong Note </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket
finished the year on a strong note, rising more than one percent
Thursday after a late rally in a strong half-day of trading.
</P>
<P>
Overall market capitalization for 1998 also soared to record
heights reaching 533 billion Australian dollars (327.42 billion
U.S. dollars) by the close of trade compared to 453.9 billion
Australian dollars (278.83 billion U.S. dollars) on December 31,
1997.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed 1998 up 29.2 points,
or 1.05 percent, at 2,813.4 on very strong turnover after an
earlier slide of more than 20 points, still well below its high
for the year of 2,881.4 points reached in April.
</P>
<P>
"Being the end of the year and end of the quarter there was a
bit of window dressing going on particularly with a lot of the
large funds," said Michael Baker from Henderson Charlton-Jones.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was a hefty 206.97 million shares traded with
a value of 390.84 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Rising stocks outnumbered falling stocks 558 to 335 and 303
stocks were steady.
</P>
<P>
Over the year the average daily value of shares traded exceeded
1 billion Australian dollars (614.3 million U.S. dollars) for the
first time.
</P>
<P>
By the close Thursday, the all industrials index gained 49
points to 5,060.1 points and the all resources added 13.9 points
to 974.7 points.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector was 62.8 points stronger at 6,434.8 points.
</P>
<P>
Westpac bank was the best performer up 14.7 cents to 10.92
Australian dollars, ANZ bank added 13 cents to 10.68 Australian
dollars, National Australia Bank stacked on 20 cents to 24.60
Australian dollars while the Commonwealth Bank was 16.3 cents
firmer at 23.16 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among resources stocks, diversified miner BHP ended the year on
a firmer note up 21.9 cents at 12.02 Australian dollars, global
miner Rio Tinto gained 25.5 cents to 19.36 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index was also higher, adding 13.6 points to 1,109.3
while the price of gold bullion added 0.90 U.S. dollars an ounce
to 287.25 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
