<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Delivers New Year's Message (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
expressed hope today that people in all nations will make further
progress in the realm of peace, stability and development during
1999.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the comment in his New Year's Eve message broadcast
live by China Radio International, China Central People's
Broadcasting Station and China Central Television.
</P>
<P>
The message -- "Working Hard Together to Ensure a Bright Future
for the World" -- represented Jiang's great confidence in the
future of China and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee, noted that 1998 marks the 20th
anniversary of China's reform and opening policies. He said China
has scored great achievements and accumulated valuable experience
in the construction of socialist modernizations over the past two
decades under the leadership of the CPC and the guidance of Deng
Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese people are more confidently marching to the future, "
said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said cross-century state leaders and the leaders of the
CPPCC National Committee were elected during the First Session of
the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) and the First Session
of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) in 1998.
</P>
<P>
China maintained comparatively rapid development in 1998 thanks
to correct measures the Chinese Government adopted in face of the
financial crisis which continues to engulf many countries in Asia,
according to the president.
</P>
<P>
He noted that progress has been made in enterprise, financial
and government institutional reforms, and Chinese citizens have
marked improvements in terms of living standards.
</P>
</TEXT>
