<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Delivers New Year's Message (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The monumental victory the Chinese army and people won this
year in fighting against the most serious flooding in some four
decades exhibited the indomitable heroic spirit of the Chinese
nation, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, which returned to the montherland last year, has
since maintained stability and prosperity in spite of the adverse
impact of the Asian financial crisis and various other emerging
challenges.
</P>
<P>
The people in Hong Kong can create a bright future with the
support of the central government and the government of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, according to
the president.
</P>
<P>
By pursuing an independent diplomatic policy of peace, he said,
China has consolidated cooperation with developing countries and
strengthed friendly relations with its neighbors. He added that
further progress has been made in developing diplomatic relations
with the United States, Russia, Europe and Japan.
</P>
<P>
He noted China also actively contributed to easing the
financial crisis in Asia by adopting a highly responsible attitude
and playing a constructive role in handling other key
international issues.
</P>
<P>
China is determined to work with the people of all countries in
promoting the lofty cause of world peace and development, said
the president.
</P>
<P>
China will further deepen reforms, expand opening and exert all
possible efforts to overcome difficulties and problems arising in
the course of advancement and promote the sustained, steady
development of the economy and society and the coordinated
development of material and ethical progress.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pledged that the Chinese Government will extend even
greater effort to help laid-off workers, farmers in
poverty-stricken areas and all other Chinese citizens facing
difficulty.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Macao will return to China, Jiang said, adding it
marks another important step the Chinese people have made on the
road to the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
