<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Delivers New Year's Message (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang stressed that China will act in accordance with the
policy of "one country, two systems" and the Basic Law of the
Macao Special Administrative Region throughout the preparation
period and will guarantee the smooth transition of power in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president reiterated that Taiwan is an inalienable
part of China, and stressed that the Chinese Government is
determined to settle the Taiwan issue in line with the policies of
"peaceful reunification, and one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely hope that Taiwan authorities will comply with the
wishes of the people, squarely face reality and resume dialogue
and negotiations with the mainland in order to help realize direct
cross-Straits mail, shipping and trade services, and formally end
the hostility between the two sides under the one China
principle," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He said that the deepening multipolarization and economic
globalization, as well as the rapid development of science and
technology are offering new development opportunities for all
countries.
</P>
<P>
"However, the world is still far from tranquil," said
Jiang. "Hegemonism and power politics continue to exist, and no
fundamental changes have been made in the old, unjust and
unreasonable international political and economic order; conflicts
related to race, religion, territorial disputes and interference
in the internal affairs of other nations surface from time to
time; international crime, terrorism, drug smuggling,
environmental deterioration and many other international questions
remain unanswered."
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed the Chinese government's deep concern about the
spread and increasing severity of the Asia financial crisis. He
called on countries throughout the world to strengthen cooperation
in overcoming the crisis and preventing a worldwide economic
recession.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope that people in all nations will work
together to nurture a world in which all people can live and work
in peace and contentment, as well as a beautiful world where human
beings will be able to continuously realize colorful civilizations
and progress. 
</P>
