<HEADLINE> Indonesia Posts 77.63 Percent of Inflation in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's inflation in
December was 1.42 percent, bringing the 1998 inflation to 77.63
percent, the Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The country's inflation in 1997 was only 11.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The December inflation was particularly triggered by an
increase in prices of commodities in the past two weeks during the
fasting month of Ramadhan," BPS Chief Sugito said.
</P>
<P>
The prices of several commodities had increased along with the
people's rising demand during the Christmas and the fasting month
of Ramadhan, he said.
</P>
<P>
The increase in the prices of commodities was reflected by
consumer's price index which reached 198.54 compared to 195.86 in
November.
</P>
<P>
He said the December inflation was higher than the November
inflation which reached 0.08 percent, but was lower than the same
period last year when the figure was recorded at 2.04 percent.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the rising prices of rice, meat, chicken, fish
and eggs had contributed a lot to the December inflation. 
</P>
