<HEADLINE> Share Prices Show Little Movement on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ended the year
with little movement in the half-day session on the Singapore
Stock Market on the eve of the year 1999.
</P>
<P>
Activity almost came to a still ahead of the new year holiday
after some window-dressing gave the market some support during the
morning trading. No fresh incentive emerged to influence dealings
afterwards.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) closed 1.97 points
lower at 1392.73 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 75.91 million units worth 99.31 million
Singapore dollars (about 60.21 million U.S. dollars). Decliners
led advancers by 130 to 82 with 208 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was a 0.81 million parcel of CSA which
transacted at 1.04 Singapore dollars per share. It was followed by
Adv SysAuto that had 0.56 million units traded. CityDev was next
with 0.16 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
ASJ Hlds was the sole stock that showed gain on the chart,
inching up six cents to end at 0.585 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Nat Kap was the biggest loser of the day
retreating nine cents to close at 0.345 Singapore dollars. CityDev
was next shedding five cents to 7.15 Singapore dollars. Adv
SysAuto sank three cents to end at 0.86 Singapore dollars.
</P>
