<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doctors Satisfied With Condition of Four Surviving Sextuplets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Doctors say they are
satisfied with the conditions of the four surviving sextuplets
eight days after their birth in the northeast city of Shenyang.
</P>
<P>
The four boys and two girls were born at around 7:30 pm on the
evening of December 23 in this capital of China's Liaoning
Province. Two of them, a boy and a girl, died of lung hemorrhages
on December 27.
</P>
<P>
"The four survivors are in much better condition than we
expected," said Dr. Mao Jian from the New-Born Intensive Care
Department of the No 2 Hospital attached to the China Medical
University.
</P>
<P>
Mao said that the little girl who was born second suffered from
arterial duct patency and heart murmur on December 28, but that on
December 30 the arterial duct closed and the heart murmur
disappeared after two day's treatment.
</P>
<P>
Hospital reports show that the second baby now has better lung
and circulatory functions and is taking milk easily. The three
others have no apnea.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Mao said that the weight of the remaining babies has
increased by 15 to 40 grams respectively.
</P>
<P>
The babies were delivered by Caesarean section when their
mother, Yao Hong, a 33-year-old woman living in the suburbs of
Shenyang, experienced delivery problems on the afternoon of
December 23.
</P>
<P>
The mother was pregnant for only 28 weeks, and the heaviest
infant had a birth weight of only 1.17 kilograms, according to
Dr. Mao.
</P>
<P>
The sextuplets were naturally conceived rather than as a result
of artificial insemination, and medical experts say that the
chances of a woman giving to birth to six children is one in 400
billion.
</P>
<P>
Doctors attributed the births to hereditary factors. Li
Quanyou, the father, is one of twins and the mother has an aunt
who is also one of twins and has twins of her own. Li and Yao
already have a 12-year-old girl.
</P>
<P>
The surviving four babies are still being strictly monitored.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
