<HEADLINE> Malaysia's New Defense Forces Chief Stresses Need to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's new Defense
Forces Chief Gen. Mohd Zahidi Haji Zainuddin stressed Thursday the
need for the armed forces to enhance their operational capability
even during the economic downturn.
</P>
<P>
This should be achieved through the optimum utilization of
existing assets, the new defense forces chief said here after
taking over the command from his predecessor Gen. Ismail Haji Omar
who retired Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mohd Zahidi said human resources should also be developed,
taking into account technological advancement in the military.
</P>
<P>
He also wanted due attention be given to aspects of
professionalism, expertise, responsibility and loyalty to the
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He said the Malaysian armed forces should continue to work
closely with government agencies and forces in neighboring and
friendly countries to enhance regional resilience.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need for maintaining commitment and
capability for peace missions under the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Mohd Zahidi, 50, was first commissioned as an officer in 1969
and since then has assumed various posts.
</P>
<P>
He attended military courses in Australia, Pakistan, the
Philippines and the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
