<HEADLINE> U.S. Embassy in Tel Aviv Closes Over Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 31 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Embassy in Tel Aviv
closed on Thursday after Ambassador Edward Walker received
"credible threats".
</P>
<P>
"The embassy received a credible and specific threat and as a
result the ambassador thought it prudent to close the embassy
today while we investigate with the appropriate authorities,"
said embassy spokesman Larry Schwartz.
</P>
<P>
Whether the threat came from an individual or an organization
or whether it targeted specific embassy staff or the building
itself are not immediately known.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli security source, requesting anonymity, said the
threats were aimed at the embassy staff. Israeli radio said the
life of Ned Walker was threatened.
</P>
<P>
Schwartz said it has not been decided on when the embassy will
reopen.
</P>
<P>
Two bombings of the U.S. embassies in Nairobi and Dar es Salaam
on Aug. 7 killed 224 people.
</P>
<P>
In the Middle East, there has been growing resentment against
the U.S. following the U.S.- British airstrikes against Iraq.
</P>
</TEXT>
