<HEADLINE> 49 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police on Thursday
seized 49 kilograms of pure heroin in an operation against drug
trafficking in eastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The police followed a tanker in Gurpinar town of Van province
linking neighboring Iran and found the heroin in 49 parcels hidden
in the vehicle, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Four suspects were detained in connection with the drug
smuggling in the town.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish police have seized over 10 tonnes of drugs
including 5.3 tonnes of hashish and 3.8 tonnes of heroin in 2,928
operations against drug trafficking by December this year.
</P>
<P>
And 5,172 Turkish people and 293 foreigners were detained
on drug smuggling charges, and 15 smugglers were killed in
clashes with the police in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs from the border areas of
Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
