<HEADLINE> Technology Exchanges Beneficial to China and U.S., FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The normal technological trade
and exchanges are in the common interests of both China and the
United States, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark in response to a question on a recent
report issued by the U.S. congress Wednesday, in which they
claimed that China tried to grab the high-tech know-hows from
Sino-U.S. technical cooperative projects, including satellite
launching. The report called the bilateral cooperation a move
that "hurts the national interests of United States."
</P>
<P>
Zhu considered such rhetorics "groundless and irresponsible",
adding that China is deeply dissatisfied with such comments.
</P>
<P>
"With a view of the overall growth of the bilateral ties in
mind, China hoped the United States to remove barriers hindering
the economic and technical exchanges between the two countries,
not vice verse," he said. 
</P>
