<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on China's Diplomacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- China will, as always, pursue
an independent foreign policy of peace in the coming year, and
make unremitted efforts along with all peace-loving countries and
people the world over to safeguard world peace and stability and
promote common development.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao made these remarks here
this afternoon at a routine press conference when asked to review
China's diplomatic achievements in 1998 and expectations in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the international situation underwent major and
profound changes in 1998, noting that the Chinese government
adhered to an independent foreign policy of peace and made
dedicated contributions to safeguarding world peace and promoting
the common development of the humanity, thus winning wide acclaims
from the international community.
</P>
<P>
China's friendly and cooperative ties with all countries in the
world were further developed, he said, and the unity and
cooperation between China and other developing nations witnessed
continued strengthening and enhancement.
</P>
<P>
China's good-neighborly and friendly ties with neighboring
countries were deepened and its relations with developed countries
further improved, added Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he noted, Sino-U.S. relations entered a new phase of
development, the relations between China and the European Union
and its member nations scored new progress, Sino-Russian relations
kept deepening and Sino-Japanese relations continued to maintain a
steady growth momentum.
</P>
<P>
In major international affairs concerning peace and stability,
he stressed, China have resolutely held that disputes should be
resolved peacefully through consultations and is in firm
opposition to resorting to force or threating to use of force.
</P>
<P>
Under the backdrop of the financial crisis impacting the whole
globe, China made its own contributions to the world and regional
economic growth and financial stability, which had drawn the
worldwide attention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
