<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Restrictions Lifted on Silk Garment Exports to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) is to lift restrictions
on the export of silk clothing to the United States.
</P>
<P>
From next year exporters will no longer require an official
export license, following a new agreement between China and the
U.S.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC officials said that the move will help China improve its
management of silk clothing exports to the U.S., simplify the
export procedure, cut the cost of operations, and will boost the
growth of bilateral trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Textiles and clothing goods are China's leading export
products to the United States, with annual exports valued at 45
billion US dollars. The export of silk garments is valued at
close to two billion US dollars a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
