<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Container Movements Hit New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 31 (Xinhua) --The Port of Shanghai handled a
record 3.06 million TEUs in 1998, making it one of the world's top
ten largest ports for container throughput.
</P>
<P>
The figure was up 21 percent from last year and total goods
handled reached 160 million tons, according to the port authority.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the port's handling capacity will rise to
3.8 million TEUs by the end of this century. 
</P>
