<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Departments Cut Business Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Following a decision of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
State Council, all of China's central departments have completed
the process of winding up their business connections, according to
the official body set up to monitor the process.
</P>
<P>
Departments of the CPC Central Committee and the State Council
will no longer be involved in the management of enterprises that
they formerly ran.
</P>
<P>
From tomorrow they are expected to end their business
associations under the supervision of the specially appointed
coordinating body.
</P>
<P>
A number of the enterprises will be transferred to national or
local management groups while loss-making firms will be suspended
or closed down.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime most of the businesses must maintain normal
operations and ensure the stability of their workforces.
</P>
<P>
The decision has been made to eliminate protectionism practiced
by certain departments, break monopolies in a number of
industries, enable central departments to perform their duties
fairly, promote the restructuring and development of
state-owned enterprises and turn enterprises into the principal
part of market competition.
</P>
<P>
The move was launched after the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party decided to prohibit the armed forces,
armed police and judicial departments from being involved in
business activities.
</P>
<P>
It is designed to strengthen Party building and building of
political power, combat corruption and separate the functions of
the government from those of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
All Party and government departments concerned support the
decision to ban their involvement in business activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
