<HEADLINE> HK Stocks End Year's Trade Just Above 10,000 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 72.86
points, or 0.72 percent, to close the half-day trade at 10,048.58
Thursday, the last trading session of the year.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover was thin due to the lack of buying interest
before the New Year holiday and amounted to 943 million HK dollars
(121 million U.S. dollars), 979 million HK dollars (131 million
U.S. dollars) less than that of Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index edged down 4.38 points, or 0.04 percent, to
open at 10,117.06 Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The share prices ended at 10,121.44 points Wednesday, shedding
104.53 points, or 1.02 percent.
</P>
<P>
This year has seen Hong Kong stock market plunge to a five-year
low of about 6,600 points in August in the aftermath of Asian
financial crisis and due to international speculative attacks on
the market.
</P>
<P>
After the government intervention, the share prices then began
to rebound and climbed up to the psychological 10,000-point mark
in late October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
