<HEADLINE> S. Korean Business Climate to Improve in Early 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a report, the country's central bank said index in a
business survey for the first three months of 1999 stands at 73,
a sharp rise from the 55 recorded for the corresponding period in
1998.
</P>
<P>
An index of 100 or above demonstrates that more companies
surveyed are doing better, according to the pollsters.
</P>
<P>
"The rise in the survey index implies that a slump in business
activities will ease considerably early next year," said the
report. The survey polled 2,893 firms, whose turnover exceeded
1.5 billion won (1.3 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Some 51.4 percent of the surveyed said the economy will bottom
out in the first half of next year while 26.7 percent predicted
it will turn around in the second half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
