<HEADLINE> South Korea Expects Lower Per Capita GNP for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The per capita GNP was measured on a basis of a GNP deflator
increase rate of six percent, population growth rate of 0.9
percent and an annual average exchange rate of 1,400 South Korean
won against the greenback.
</P>
<P>
This year's per capita GNP is expected to plunge by 33.5
percent following the financial crisis, which was caused
primarily by corporate bankruptcies and bad loans last year. The
per capita GNP in 1997 was reportedly 9,511.00 dollars.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's per capita GNP ranked 34th in the world last
year, and it is expected to slip to the 42nd this year. 
</P>
