the region to resolve the Afghan conflict. The visit will be part
of consultations on Afghanistan as the two countries have been
coordinating efforts on the Afghan issue for a long time.
</P>
<P>
Despite different approach towards the Afghan issue, Pakistan
and Iran have joined hands to find out negotiated settlement of
the Afghan crisis, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Iran had constituted joint mission for Afghan
peace efforts earlier this year, which had paid a visit to
Kandahar and Mazar-i-Sharif for talks with the Taliban and the
anti-Taliban Northern Alliance.
</P>
<P>
The peace efforts had resulted into the first face-to-face
meeting between the Taliban and the Northern Alliance in Islamabad
at the end of April this year.
</P>
<P>
However, the talks had collapsed after five days due to their
intransigent attitude. 
