<HEADLINE> LIFFE Is Ready for The Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON December 30 (Xinhua) - The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) announced Wednesday
that it is ready for the introduction of the euro on 4 January
1999.
</P>
<P>
In line with other European exchanges, LIFFE will be closed for
trading on Thursday 31st December and Friday 1st January. It will
re-open for trading, as normal, on Monday 4 January.
</P>
<P>
Hugh Freedberg, LIFFE's Chief Executive, said: "As an
international futures and options exchange, trading products
denominated in euro zone currencies, LIFFE has been preparing for
the euro for over two and a half years."
</P>
<P>
As far back as 1996 LIFFE changed the legal provisions of its
contracts to allow for settlement against the euro for it
euro-denominated short term interest rate contracts (STIRS).
Therefore, LIFFE will not need to make further changes to its
contracts over the coming historic weekend.
</P>
<P>
Freedberg said, the next important date for the Exchange and
its Members will be the weekend of 23rd/24th January when LIFFE
will be converting all the open interest in its Euromark and
Eurolira contracts into LIFFE'S Euro Libor contracts.
</P>
<P>
This will create the largest pool of euro money market
liquidity anywhere in the world, providing new opportunities for
trading within these markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
