<HEADLINE> Greece's Second Biggest Airport Closed Due to Fog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Thessaloniki international
airport, the second biggest one in Greece, was shut down on
Wednesday due to heavy fog.
</P>
<P>
Most of the domestic and international flights to and from the
airport had been cancelled because landings were impossible, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) quoted the airport
officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
The airport, which was also closed due to fog on Monday, is
plagued by fog problem in winter every year.
</P>
<P>
It is hoped that a modern electronic system to be installed
next year will solve the problem. 
</P>
